In [44]:
# backtesting.py 
class SmaCross(Strategy):
    a1= 10
    a2= 20
    def init(self):
        price = self.data.Close
        self.ma1 = self.I(SMA, price, self.a1)
        self.ma2 = self.I(SMA, price, self.a2)

    def next(self):
        if crossover(self.ma1, self.ma2):
            self.buy()
        elif crossover(self.ma2, self.ma1):
            self.sell()
            
bt = Backtest(data, SmaCross, commission=.002,
              exclusive_orders=True)
stats = bt.run()

Optimization process¶

I set a range of possibile values

  • a1 range[20-100] steps = 10
  • a2 range[20-500] steps = 20

I use the function "optimize" to find the period of the moving averages that maximize the 'Equity Final[$]'

In [51]:
%%time 
stats = bt.optimize(a1=range(20, 100, 10),
                    a2=range(20,500, 20),
                    maximize = 'Equity Final [$]',
                    constraint=lambda param: param.a1 < param.a2)

# values from the optimization process
optimazeda1 = stats._strategy.a1 
optimazeda2 = stats._strategy.a2


class SmaCross(Strategy):
    a1= optimazeda1
    a2= optimazeda2
    def init(self):
        price = self.data.Close
        self.ma1 = self.I(SMA, price, self.a1)
        self.ma2 = self.I(SMA, price, self.a2)

    def next(self):
        if crossover(self.ma1, self.ma2):
            self.buy()
        elif crossover(self.ma2, self.ma1):
            self.sell()
            
bt = Backtest(data, SmaCross, commission=.02,
              exclusive_orders=True)
stats = bt.run()
